<br>
1. Create a directory on your C drive called &quot;Drivers&quot;.<br>
2. Under the &quot;Drivers&quot; directory create directories called &quot;Video&quot;, &quot;Audio&quot;, and &quot;DirectX&quot;.<br>
3. Now we'll download into those directories and you'll know precisely where everything is.<br>
4. Copy and paste this address into your browser: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://ftp://205.158.109.140/Windows/21.83/Win9x_21.83.exe">ftp://205.158.109.140/Windows/21.83/Win9x_21.83.exe</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  This is the latest NVidia drivers for Win95/98/ME.<br>
5. When prompted, choose to save the file, and save it into the &quot;C:\  Drivers\Video&quot; directory you just created.  DO NOT RUN the file yet.<br>
