<br>
Time to get to work.<br>
<br>
=================================<br>
Removing your Current Video Drivers<br>
=================================<br>
1. Right-click on your desktop and click [Properties] on the pop-up menu.  This will launch the [Display Properties] dialog.<br>
2. Click the [Settings] tab.<br>
3. Click the [Advanced...] button in the lower-right corner.<br>
4. Click the [Adapter] tab.<br>
5. Click the [Change...] button in the upper-right corner.  This will launch the [Update Device Driver] wizard.<br>
6. Click the [Next &gt;] button.<br>
7. Select [Display a list of all the drivers in a particular location...] and click the [Next &gt;] button.<br>
8. Select [Show all hardware.] in the lower-left corner.<br>
9. In the [Manufacturers:] listbox, select [Standard display types]. (it's at the top)<br>
10. In the [Models:] listbox, select [Standard Display Adapter (VGA)].<br>
11. Click the [Next &gt;] button.<br>
12. At this point, you may get a warning message asking if you are sure you want to use this driver.  If so, confirm it by clicking the [Yes] button.<br>
13. The dialog should now being showing you the driver you selected and its location.  Click the [Next &gt;] button.<br>
14. The dialog should now say it's done installing the new driver.  /cheer  Click the [Finish] button to close this dialog.<br>
15. This should bring you back to the properties page for the display adapter.  Click the [Apply] button to close this dialog.<br>
16. This should bring you back to the [Display Properties] dialog.  Click the [Close] button.<br>
17. At this point, you should be prompted to restart your computer.  Click the [Yes] button to restart.<br>
18. NOTE: When your computer restarts, it will be at 640x480 resolution. (very big icons on the desktop) This is normal.  The default Windows video drivers do not support higher resolutions.<br>
<br>
=================================<br>
Installing DirectX 8.1<br>
=================================<br>
1. Click the [Start] button, and select [Run...].<br>
2. Click the [Browse...] button and navigate to the folder where you saved the DirectX download. (C:\ Drivers\DirectX)<br>
3. Select the DirectX download (dx81eng.exe) and click the [Open] button to close this dialog.<br>
4. This will bring you back to the [Run] dialog.  Click the [OK] button to launch the application.<br>
5. You will be prompted to confirm that you wish to install DirectX 8.1.  Click the [Yes] button.<br>
6. Click the [Yes] button the accept the End Users License Agreement.<br>
7. Watch the progress bars fill up. (easy step)<br>
8. When you are prompted to restart your machine, click the [OK] button.  (like you have a choice)<br>
9. Get fresh coffee, we're halfway there.  /cheer<br>
<br>
=================================<br>
Reinstalling Your Video Drivers<br>
=================================<br>
1. Click the [Start] button, and select [Run...].<br>
2. Click the [Browse...] button and navigate to the folder where you saved the NVidia download. (C:\ Drivers\Video)<br>
3. Select the NVidia download (Win9x_21.83.exe) and click the [Open] button to close this dialog.<br>
4. This will bring you back to the [Run] dialog.  Click the [OK] button to launch the application.<br>
5. When the installation is done initializing you will get a welcome dialog.  Click the [Next &gt;] button.<br>
6. Follow along in the wizard.  I can't load these drivers, so I don't know the details of the process.<br>
7. NOTE: It's possible that during the installation you'll be prompted that a file you are trying to install is older then the currently installed file.  If this occurs, click the [Yes] button to retain the current file.<br>
8. You'll probably be prompted to restart again when the installation is done.<br>
9. When your machine restarts, you'll probably need to readjust your screen resolution.  Right-click on your desktop and click [Properties] on the pop-up menu.  This will launch the [Display Properties] dialog.<br>
10. Click the [Settings] tab.<br>
11. Adjust the [Screen area] slider to your preferred resolution.<br>
12. Click the [Apply] button.<br>
13. Confirm the resizing by clicking the [OK] button.<br>
14. Verify that you want to keep this resolution by clicking the [Yes] button.<br>
<br>
=================================<br>
Installing Your Audio Drivers<br>
=================================<br>
1. Click the [Start] button, and select [Run...].<br>
2. Click the [Browse...] button and navigate to the folder where you saved the SoundBlaster download. (C:\ Drivers\Audio)<br>
3. Select the SoundBlaster download (SBLWMEdrv.exe) and click the [Open] button to close this dialog.<br>
4. This will bring you back to the [Run] dialog.  Click the [OK] button to launch the application.<br>
5. Follow along in the wizard.  I can't load these drivers, so I don't know the details of the process.<br>
7. NOTE: It's possible that during the installation you'll be prompted that a file you are trying to install is older then the currently installed file.  If this occurs, click the [Yes] button to retain the current file.<br>
8. You'll probably be prompted to restart again when the installation is done.<br>
<br>
